<h1>LG Washer Shock Absorber Replacement</h1>

<p>When an LG washer shakes hard, walks across the floor, or bangs on the spin cycle, worn shock absorbers (the suspension that steadies the drum) are a frequent cause once the load and leveling check out. We replace the shock absorbers same-day across LA — $280–360 with a one-year warranty — and check the rest of the suspension while we're in there. Call (323) 990-7550.</p>

<h2>Signs Your Shock Absorbers Are Worn</h2>
<p>Worn shocks let the drum swing too far on spin, so the machine shakes violently or bangs even when the load is balanced and the floor is level, and you'll often see a <a href="/washer/error-codes/lg-washer-ue-error/">UE code</a> as it tries to compensate. The drum may visibly walk or wander. This is the most common hardware cause behind an <a href="/washer/symptoms/lg-washer-shaking/">LG washer shaking and loud on spin</a> once the simple stuff is ruled out.</p>

<h2>How We Replace the Shock Absorbers</h2>
<p>First our techs confirm it isn't a balance problem or shipping bolts left in after delivery — both cause identical shaking and cost nothing to fix. If the suspension is genuinely worn, we replace the shock absorbers or damper rods as a set and check the springs and counterweight while we're in there. It's about a 1–1.5 hour job.</p>

<h2>Cost of Shock Absorber Replacement</h2>
<p>Shock absorber replacement runs $280–360 installed, including replacing the worn shocks as a set, and the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. For how this sits among other LG washer prices, see our <a href="/washer/price-list/lg-washer-repair-cost/">LG washer repair cost</a> page.</p>

<h2>Why Replace as a Set</h2>
<p>Shocks wear at the same rate, so if one is worn enough to cause shaking, the others aren't far behind. Replacing a single shock leaves the drum unevenly damped and sets up another callback within months, so we always do them as a set to keep the machine balanced and quiet.</p>

<h2>OEM Parts and Warranty</h2>
<p>We fit OEM shock absorbers, not generic dampers that wear quickly, and back the work with a one-year warranty on parts and labor. Fresh suspension also protects the bearing and tub from the extra movement worn shocks allow.</p>

<p>Washer banging or walking across the floor? Our LG Dryer Repair techs check the suspension on-site across LA, Orange County, and Ventura County before quoting. Call (323) 990-7550; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Shock Absorber Replacement</h2>

<h3>How do I know if my LG washer shock absorbers are worn?</h3>
<p>Worn shock absorbers make an LG washer shake violently or bang during the spin cycle even when the load is balanced and the machine is level. The drum moves too far because the suspension no longer dampens it, and you'll often get a UE code as the washer tries to compensate.</p>

<h3>How much does LG washer shock absorber replacement cost?</h3>
<p>Shock absorber replacement runs $280–360 installed, including replacing the worn shocks as a set. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair, and the work has a one-year warranty. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Why do you replace all the shock absorbers, not just one?</h3>
<p>Because they wear at the same rate — if one is worn enough to cause shaking, the others aren't far behind. Replacing a single shock leaves the machine unbalanced and sets up another callback, so we do them as a set.</p>

<h3>Could my shaking LG washer just be a balance or leveling problem instead?</h3>
<p>Yes, and we check that first — an unbalanced load, an unlevel floor, or shipping bolts left in after delivery all cause shaking and cost nothing to fix. We only replace shocks when the machine shakes with a balanced load on a level floor.</p>

<h3>Is it worth replacing the shock absorbers?</h3>
<p>Yes — at $280–360 versus $800–1,500 for a new LG washer, fresh suspension stops the shaking and protects the bearing and tub from the extra movement. Left alone, worn shocks let the drum batter other parts and lead to bigger repairs.</p>

